<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-16T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-16T20:00:00-05:00" n="1209" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1209">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">823.51/1388a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">McGurk</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-16T20:00:00-05:00">December 16, 1940—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>149. The Export-Import Bank has approved the extension of a credit of
                            $10,000,000 to the Central Reserve Bank of Peru at 4 percent <pb facs="1154" n="1142" xml:id="pg_1142"/> interest and to be amortized
                            over a 6 year period. The proceeds of the credit are to be used for
                            general imports of United States goods, and the earlier $2,000,000
                            credit is to be canceled. Details of the arrangement are being worked
                            out with Beltrán, and no public announcement is to be made at this
                            time.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
